Christopher Flowers was driving along Chili Avenue in Rochester on March 9 when he dropped a lit cigarette into his shirt . 
  Several layers of his clothing burst into flames and engulfed his torso . 
  He was rushed to hospital with severe burns to his torso and neck . 
  But on Sunday, hospital officials announced he has died in hospital . 
  Flowers was traveling down the road when he accidentally set himself on fire . 
 